Opcode [8 Bits] Operand1 [8 Bits] Operand2 [8 Bits] Operand3 [8 Bits]

OPC → Opcode
OPR → Operand

Registers:                   (Hex Index)
PC → Program Counter             [0x0]
A → General Purpose Register     [0x1]
B → General Purpose Register     [0x2]
C → General Purpose Register     [0x3]
D → General Purpose Register     [0x4]
E → General Purpose Register     [0x5]
ACC → Accumulator Register      [0x6..+]

Instruction Set Architecture:

  (Opcode)

MOV: (0x00) → Move Value OPR2 into Register Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index) [0x1-0x6]
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

JMP: (0x01) → Change PC value to OPR1
   Operand 1: (Hex Value)

JMPG: (0x08) → Change PC to value OPR1 if ACC has a value GREATER or EQUAL to 1 stored.
    Operand 1: (Hex Value)

JMPZ : (0x09) → Change PC to value OPR1 if ACC has 0 stored.
   Operand 1: (Hex Value)

Arithmetic Instructions:

ADD: (0x02) → Add Value OPR2 to value of Register Index OPR1 → Stored in ACC
   Operand 1: (Register Index) [0x1-0x6]
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

SUB: (0x03) → Subtract Value OPR2 from value of Register Index OPR1 → Stored in ACC
   Operand 1: (Hex Value)

MUL: (0x04) → Multiply Value OPR2 with value of Register Index OPR1 → Stored in ACC
   Operand 1: (Hex Value)

DIV: (0x05) → Divide Value of Register Index OPR1 from value OPR2 OPR1 → Stored in ACC
   Operand 1: (Register Index) [0x1-0x6]
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

Accumulator Movement Instructions:

LOAD: (0x06) → Load Value from Register Index OPR1 into ACC
   Operand 1: (Register Index) [0x1-0x6]

STORE: (0x07) → Store Value from ACC into Register Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index) [0x1-0x6]

RAM Instructions:

RAM_WRITE: (0xa) → Store Value from ACC into RAM Memory Address OPR1 from RAM Index OPR2
   Operand 1: (Hex Value) [Memory Address]
   Operand 2: (Hex Value) [Ram Index]

RAM_READ: (0xb) → Store Value from RAM Memory Index OPR1 from RAM Address OPR2 into ACC
   Operand 1: (Hex Value) [Memory Address]
   Operand 2: (Hex Value) [Ram Index]


RGB VIDEO Instructions:

SCREEN_CLEAR: (0xc) → Reset the Display Screen

SCREEN_DRAW: (0xd) → Reset the Display Screen
Due to this being a special function the arguments are the following:
   Value held in Register A → RED    (R)
   Value held in Register B → GREEN  (G)
   Value held in Register C → GREEN  (B)

   Value held in Register D → X Coordinate  (X)
   Value held in Register E → Y Coordinate  (Y)

